HEADWORD: Actinia
<hw>Ac*tin"i*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
L. <plw>Actini⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, E. <plw>Actinias</plw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Latinized fr. Gr. <?/, <?/, ray.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An animal of the class Anthozoa,
and family <fam>Actinid⟦ae⟧</fam>. From a resemblance to flowers in form
and color, they are often called <altname>animal flowers</altname> and
<altname>sea anemones</altname>. [See <er>Polyp</er>.].</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A genus in the family
<fam>Actinid⟦ae⟧</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
